        <p>The epiphany for the teamup∞ model came when attending a conference in New York. The room was jammed. Standing room only with every seat taken, every wall leant against. The demand from business to understand the psychology of high performance in teams was palpable.</p>

        <p>The idea sparked while listening to a panel of Neuroscientists discussing optimal differentiation in chickens, and how the coups with a higher proportion of Alpha males produced less eggs. In other words, beware of ‘All-Star’ teams – that is not the route to high performance. Ali & Andy looked around the room of 100+ senior business leaders and knew that there was a deep well of more profound insights they could organize from the neuroscience which leaders could apply for teaming.</p>
